<task id="task_E9A0CA13E74A49648F8E041081CA2064">
  <title>Target Based on Geography</title>
  <shortdesc>You can target your campaign based on the visitor's locations. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Target" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Advanced" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody>
    <context id="context_A267E6C999FC45B1AA2533B5FBD1ABFD">
      <p>
        <note>Geo Targeting is an add-on feature. To add geo targeting, contact
			 your account representative. 
		  </note>
      </p>
      <p>Geo location parameters allow you to target campaigns and experiences
		  based on your visitors' geography. You can include or exclude visitors based on
		  their country, state/province, city, DMA, or zip/postal code. This data is sent
		  with each mbox request and is based on the visitor's IP address. Select these
		  parameters just like any targeting values. 
		</p>
      <p>You can target based on one or more of the following geographical
		  units: 
		</p>
      <p>
        <ul id="ul_103DF3C430DE44128AA0F0B63E6A3511">
          <li id="li_30D5005E3DB749A8912DD99320B30908"> Country 
		  </li>
          <li id="li_B4169FA4BFAB438EAA65B9EE8CFBAF47">State 
		  </li>
          <li id="li_2057C1729ADB480D9E52A3FEC6B56F84"> City 
		  </li>
          <li id="li_C06AEF521E1E4181B0D1890AE2DAF098"> Zip Code 
		  </li>
          <li id="li_EF7ED9CBD05C45F49B71A29EDA0E71FB"> DMA 
		  </li>
          <li id="li_8F4F609493B74B4D86D1286CBAB73BD3"> Latitude 
		  </li>
          <li id="li_A8F9F1CC4005414694F1B1FA306C35CD"> Longitude 
		  </li>
        </ul>
      </p>
    </context>
    <steps id="steps_E4B81C9F93FB47FC99B2B3F8F311A6E6">
      <step id="step_3B2869FE1D674E1F8ACD23740662DF9E">
        <cmd>Click 
			 <uicontrol>Target this campaign</uicontrol>. 
		  </cmd>
      </step>
      <step id="step_396E528361764CAD93A951B497BA35A0">
        <cmd>Click 
			 <uicontrol>Geo</uicontrol>. 
		  </cmd>
      </step>
      <step id="step_1EAFAE555AEE48F38788156058C098DD">
        <cmd>Select a geographical option from the dropdown list, then select
			 an evaluator and type the desired value. 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult>
          <p>As you type, matching values are listed. 
			 </p>
          <p>For a reference of available locations and spelling, see in these
				csv files: 
			 </p>
          <p>
            <ul id="ul_71C549BB94054BF380BBCFA3DBBC6C12">
              <li id="li_79EDE8CDAAFE4369BFDCE45F68C2DFF3">
                <xref href="http://marketing.adobe.com/resources/help/en_US/tnt/csv/city_codes.csv" scope="external" format="html">City codes</xref>
              </li>
              <li id="li_1FEF6D86E7A84826AD955620D59EEEE5">
                <xref href="http://marketing.adobe.com/resources/help/en_US/tnt/csv/region_codes.csv" scope="external" format="html">Region codes</xref>
              </li>
              <li id="li_9E418215179D42598267DCFD2B72F22C">
                <xref href="http://marketing.adobe.com/resources/help/en_US/tnt/csv/country_codes.csv" scope="external" format="html">Country codes</xref>
              </li>
              <li id="li_B020374E4D524F7085E68469E7F40C76">
                <xref href="http://marketing.adobe.com/resources/help/en_US/tnt/csv/metro_codes.csv" scope="external" format="html">Metro codes</xref>
                <p>
                  <note>Use the "Metro codes" csv file to target by DMA. Use the
						location spellings listed in the 
						<wintitle>METRO_NAME</wintitle> column of the csv file. 
					 </note>
                </p>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </p>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
      <step id="step_41D2FF663D794F82932DCFD4B6701126">
        <cmd>(Optional) Add additional conditions. 
		  </cmd>
      </step>
      <step id="step_D2DAB2B5B0924CD2B4111E225209497D">
        <cmd>Click 
			 <uicontrol>Done</uicontrol>. 
		  </cmd>
      </step>
    </steps>
